SIMPLE: outfit
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outfit
<hw>Out"fit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fitting
out, or equipment, as of a ship for a voyage, or of a person for an
expedition in an unoccupied region or residence in a foreign land; the
expense of, or allowance made for, equipment, as by the government of
the United States to a diplomatic agent going abroad.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Any assemblage of objects
required for or used in performing a task; things required as equipment
for a task.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A complete ensemble of clothing, selected to form a
matching set; a coordinated costume; <as>as, a new Easter
<ex>outfit</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A business enterprise; <as>as, what <ex>outfit</ex>
do you work for?</as>.</def> <mark>[informal]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Any team or party of people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>outfitted</ent>⟦br⟧
